    • Constructor Detail

      • ClimberS

        public ClimberS()
        Creates a new ClimberS. This is the elevator on our robot uses for climbing in endgame.

        This subsystem uses PID to lift the elevator and then do a pullup on the bar, giving us 25 points.

    • Method Detail

      • brake

        public void brake()
        Start braking the elevator.

        NOTE: This method sets the solenoid output to false.

      • unbrake

        public void unbrake()
        Unbrake the elevator.

        NOTE: This sets the solenoid output to true.

      • setClimberPower

        public void setClimberPower​(double power)
        Set the raw elevator power as a number from -1 to 1 inclusive.
        Parameters:
        power - The power to apply. It is clamped within (-1,1)

      • setClimberPowerFeedForward

        public void setClimberPowerFeedForward​(double power)
        Sets the elevator power from -1 to 1 but adds Feed Forward to the input so it will apply enough power to hold its position with an input of 0.
        Parameters:
        power - The power to add Feed Forward to and apply

      • runUpPID

        public void runUpPID()
        This method runs the Elevator PID up to the upper set point in RobotPreferences. It also updates PIDF, i-zone and set point with current values from preferences.

      • runDownPID

        public void runDownPID()
        This method runs the PID down to the lower set point stored in robot preferences. It updates PIDF, i-zone and the set point with the values stored in preferences, but uses different values from runUpPID.

      • isAtSetPoint

        public boolean isAtSetPoint​(ClimberS.climberLevel setPoint)
        Checks whether the climber is at a given set point. This must be called continuously to check accurately, as it measures whether it has been in roughly the same spot for 15 loops.

        Note: Don't forget to call isAtSetPoint(ClimberS.climberLevel.reset) before checking to make sure the loop count is at 0. (this returns false)
        Parameters:
        setPoint - what ClimberS.climberLevel to check.
        Returns:
        whether the climber is at the given set point

      • getVelocity

        public double getVelocity()
        Check the velocity of the encoder connected to the climber talon. Units are ticks/100ms
        Returns:
        the velocity of the climber encoder
